olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
1 stalk celery
1 tin cannellini beans
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet onion & garlic paste
¼ cup water
1 tin coconut milk
1 tsp brown sugar
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
20 g plant-based butter
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag coriander

• Trim green beans and slice into thirds. Thinly slice celery. Grate the carrot. Drain and rinse cannellini beans.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Cook green beans, carrot and celery, stirring, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add tomato paste, chermoula spice blend and onion & garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water, coconut milk, brown sugar, vegetable stock powder and cannellini beans and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, 3-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat and stir through baby spinach leaves and plant-based butter. Season to taste.

• In a medium frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Add a mini flour tortilla and cook until golden, 1 minute each side.
• Transfer to a plate and repeat with remaining tortillas, adding extra oil as necessary.

• Divide Moroccan-style cannellini bean stew between bowls.
• Tear over coriander and serve with tortilla flatbreads. Enjoy!